Download and install scala-2.10.4

  wget http://downloads.typesafe.com/scala/2.11.7/scala-2.11.7.rpm
  rpm -ivh scala-2.11.7.rpm 
  
  type 'scala' and it takes you to the scala repl.
  You can quit using ':q'


Download and install Kafka

	wget http://mirror.cogentco.com/pub/apache/kafka/0.8.2.2/kafka_2.11-0.8.2.2.tgz
 	tar -xf kafka_2.11-0.8.2.2.tgz   

	Extract kafka tarball and move the extracted directory to /opt/kafka.

	Modify /opt/kafka/config/server.properties to reflect zookeeper quorum settings

		log.dirs=/opt/kafka/logs

		zookeeper.connect=localhost:5181


Start Kafka server

 	bin/kafka-server-start.sh config/server.properties > logs/kafka-server.log 2>&1 &
   

Create a topic called “hbasesets”

	bin/kafka-topics.sh --zookeeper localhost:5181 --create --topic lab2 --partitions 3 --replication-factor 1

Verify the topic has been created

  	bin/kafka-topics.sh --zookeeper localhost:5181 --list

List Kafka topic details and partitions

 	bin/kafka-topics.sh --zookeeper localhost:5181 --describe --topic lab2

